Rating: 4
This is a truly fabulous recipe! I had it last week at a friends house and just now finished making one for a dinner party tomorrow night. Just some tips: It also took me about 20 minutes to get the curd thickened, and it only reached about 165- and that was over a very aggressive simmer. Thickened very nicely in fridge. I also modified the layers to save on freeze time- I did one layer of ice cream, lemon curd and then the meringue. That way, as long as your crust is cool, you could do the ice cream and lemon curd at one time, pop it into the freezer while you make the meringue, and then top with meringue and freeze. I also plan to broil the meringue, not use a 500 degree oven, that way the heat will all be on top, as opposed to the whole oven being hot. Also, if you are nervous about freezing the meringue, if you have a stand mixer, it only takes about 5 minutes to make, so you could easily make it right before serving. Yummy!

