I've made lemon curd for years and never felt the need to take its temperature. So when it cooked to the thick-and-glisteny stage (which I regard as done), I put in the instant thermometer and read 160, far short of the 178-180 decreed by the recipe. So I cooked it another 5 minutes, and the temp went up hardly at all. I feared for overcooking the eggs, and I stopped at that point. The curd was just fine when I spread it on -- not overly sticky as some reported. So I question the 178-180 degrees stated in the recipe. I took the pie (already meringued) out of the freezer 20 minutes before finishing it in the 500 degree oven. That was probably a mistake, because the ice cream was nearly melted. That probably wouldn't happen if you use the torch method to brown the meringue. But very good nonetheless!

