I also made this pie for Easter dinner. It received raves reviews by all at the table from age 7 to 89! I made the lemon curd five days in advance and completed the whole pie including the meringue two days ahead of time. I used a butane torch immediately prior to serving the pie--skipped the oven entirely. This recipe is a sure "keeper"! The flavors were outstanding together. I am going to try the crust with other fillings as well as the pecan flavors added immensely to the pie.

